Hi Community,

Could someone confirm expected behavior here?

End Goal:To double check if the javascript code I created here would allow for when users login on a certain external page with the HubSpot tracking code on it, that the "event" is recorded and passed back to HubSpot.When someone who is already a contact in HubSpot logs in on this page it should be tracked. If the person is not a contact in HubSpot would this create them as a new contact?

(<https://cultuurwerkt.nl/>)Using the events tool feature for custom events
'//Variable declaration.
let email = NULL;

//Trigger event on click...
document.querySelectorAll('button[type="submit"]').onclick = function() {

//Check to see if the button clicked, was the login button.
if(this.form.action === '/inloggen/'){

//Get email address from form.
let email = document.getElementById("id_username").value;

    //Send this over to HubSpot.
    _hsq.push(["trackEvent", {

id: "000006840831",
email: email

 }]);

 }
};
